        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 1:19AM CST by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 119 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ballinger, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ballinger, Winters, Novice, Hatchel, Silver Valley, Crews, Glen Cove,
Benoit, Goldsboro, Lake Winters Lake, and Hords Creek Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
